<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="67" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1268,1643]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1384,1410]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[378,481,1385,1411]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[519,638,1385,1410]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Hemiosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fittkaui">
<emphasis box="[519,638,1385,1410]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">H. fittkaui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from Rio Itu in Amazonas State, 
<collectingCountry box="[1200,1275,1385,1411]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Oliva" box="[1286,1436,1385,1411]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68" refString="Oliva, A. (1994) A revision of the genus Hemiosus Sharp, 1882 in South America (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae). Bulletin et Annales de la Societe royale belge d'Entomologie, 130, 267 - 303." type="journal article" year="1994">
Oliva (
<number box="[1366,1427,1385,1411]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" value="1994.0">1994</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
considered this species (like others occurring in northern South 
<collectingCountry box="[894,997,1424,1450]" name="United States of America" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">America</collectingCountry>
) as a relictual species associated with a putative South 
<collectingCountry box="[356,459,1462,1488]" name="United States of America" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">America</collectingCountry>
refugium, because their preference for sandy bottom habitats might restrict their dispersion (
<bibRefCitation author="Oliva" box="[286,421,1501,1527]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68" refString="Oliva, A. (1994) A revision of the genus Hemiosus Sharp, 1882 in South America (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae). Bulletin et Annales de la Societe royale belge d'Entomologie, 130, 267 - 303." type="journal article" year="1994">Oliva 1994</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Oliva" box="[432,496,1501,1527]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68" refString="Oliva, A. (2007) Distribucion de Berosini (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae) en America del Sur. Revista de la sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 66 (3 - 4), 47 - 56." type="journal article" year="2007">2007</bibRefCitation>
). However in this case, the restricted distribution she found is most likely related to a lack of sampling; 
<taxonomicName box="[417,624,1540,1565]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Hemiosus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fittkaui">
<emphasis box="[417,624,1540,1565]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Hemiosus fittkaui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is herein the first record from Bahia State, 
<collectingCountry box="[1141,1217,1540,1566]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Although, habitat notes were not given in the collecting labels, the material was collected from the potamal region of the river (A. L. Carvalho, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
